HELP=$"
gone	[spells]	*	installed spells that lack a spell definition"

LONG=$"
augur gone displays installed spells that lack a spell definition.
Unless the SA has reason to retain installation
then gone spells aught to be dispelled.

# augur gone | sed 's:^:dispel/' | au queue; dispel

The above command automatically queues for dispel
spells that are gone and then executes dispel
so the files installed by those spells are removed from the box.

When a gone spell triggers an ELF Miss event
the gone spell can not be re-cast.
This condition blocks the cleaning of /aux/old/
This wastes space and creates the potential for
what aught to be a non exploitable security risk.

# au begin immune-exam-dispel

The above command enables the immune system
to do accomplish the task automatically."


param(){ :;}

run(){

show_gone(){
 export LC_ALL=C
 local AVAILABLE

 local AVAILABLE=$( show_grimoire )

 if (( 3000 > $( echo "$AVAILABLE" | wc -l ) )); then
  echo "Amount of spells provided by the grimoire seems excessively low." 1>&2
  echo "augur gone check is aborting without providing results." 1>&2
  exit 1
 fi

 if   [ -n "$SPELLS" ]
 then echo "$SPELLS"; echo "$AVAILABLE"; echo "$AVAILABLE"
 else show_installed; echo "$AVAILABLE"; echo "$AVAILABLE"
 fi | sort | uniq -u
}

 SPELLS="$( ( if [ -n "$1" ]; then printf "%s\n" "$@" ; fi
              if ! tty -s;    then cat -; fi
            ) | sort -u | sed "/^$/d" )"

 show_gone
}
